<title>SOUTH AFRICA: Nu-world raises yr shr, offers scrip div.</title>
<headline>Nu-world raises yr shr, offers scrip div.</headline>
<dateline>JOHANNESBURG 1996-10-07</dateline>
<text>
<p>Year ended August 31</p>
<p>			(million rand unless stated)</p>
<p>    Shr, attrib (cts)     52.9	  vs  36.3</p>
<p>    Shr, weighted (cts)   55.0	  vs  37.5</p>
<p>    Div (cts)		 10.6	  vs   8.1</p>
<p>    After-tax income	 9.34	 vs   5.39</p>
<p>    Pre-tax		   10.94	 vs   7.24</p>
<p>    Tax			  1.59	 vs   1.84</p>
<p>    Interest paid	    4.21	 vs   3.99</p>
<p>    Turnover		 247.46	 vs 174.48</p>
<p>    Retained earnings	7.47	 vs   4.19</p>
<p>Div payable Nov 8</p>
<p>on register Nov 1</p>
<p>Full name: Nu-world Holdings Ltd</p>
<p>NOTE - The company said its directors had resolved to award capitalisation shares to ordinary shareholders. Shareholders are entitled to accept a cash dividend instead. The terms of the capitalisation share award will be published on October 14.</p>
<p>-- Johannesburg newsroom +27 11 482 1003</p>
